{"sectionId":762,"sectionIdLiteral":"762","humanId":"lesson-339","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"I will receive whatever I request.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 339"},"annotation":"W-339","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-339\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"762#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>No one desires pain.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>But he can think that pain is pleasure.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>No one would avoid his happiness.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>But he can think that joy is painful, threatening and dangerous.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Everyone will receive what he requests.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>But he can be confused indeed about the things he wants; the state he would attain.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>What can he then request that he would want when he receives it?</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>He has asked for what will frighten him, and bring him suffering.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#1:9\"><span class=\"snr\">9</span>Let us resolve today to ask for what we really want, and only this, that we may spend this day in fearlessness, without confusing pain with joy, or fear with love.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"762#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, this is Your day.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"762#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>It is a day in which I would do nothing by myself, but hear Your Voice in everything I do; requesting only what You offer me, accepting only Thoughts You share with me.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"No one desires pain. But he can think that pain is pleasure. No one would avoid his happiness. But he can think that joy is painful, threatening and dangerous. Everyone will receive what he requests.","contentType":"acim-content","seoTitle":"Lesson 339: I will receive whatever I request | ACIM","seoDescription":"‚ú® A Course in Miracles with üéß Audio! Read and listen to Lesson¬†339 ‚ÄúI will receive whatever I request‚Äù: No one desires pain. But he can think that pain is pleasure. No one would avoid‚Ä¶","desktopBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"12. What Is the Ego?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":753,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-ego"]}},{"label":"Lesson 339","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":762,"slugs":["lesson-339","i-will-receive-whatever-i-request"]}}],"mobileBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"12. What Is the Ego?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":753,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-ego"]}},{"label":"Lesson 339","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":762,"slugs":["lesson-339","i-will-receive-whatever-i-request"]}}],"seoBreadcrumbs":[{"label":"A Course in Miracles","leadsTo":"dashboard"},{"label":"Workbook","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":401,"slugs":["workbook","introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"Part II","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":631,"slugs":["workbook","part-ii-introduction"],"forceToc":true}},{"label":"12. What Is the Ego?","leadsTo":{"locale":"en","sectionId":753,"slugs":["workbook","what-is-the-ego"]}},{"label":"Lesson 339","leadsTo":{"loca